{
  "texts": [
    "Despite the elegance of quaternions and dual quaternions in compactly representing rotations and translations, their adoption in robotics has been limited compared to homogenous transformations.",
    "A manipulator consists of a series of links connected in sequence by either revolute or prismatic joints, extending from the base frame to the end-effector.",
    "The process of determining the end-effector's position and orientation based on the joint variables is known as forward kinematics.",
    "For systematic implementation of forward kinematics in robotic mechanisms, an appropriate kinematic model is essential.",
    "The DH method employs four parameters, denoted as a i-1, ³ i-1, d i, and ¹ i, which represent the link length, link twist, link offset, and joint angle, respectively."
  ]
}